quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  7,196,"My protector is God who sent down the Book, for it is He who protects the righteous"
  7,197,"Those whom you call on besides Him have no power to help you, nor can they help themselves"
  7,198,"If you call them to the right path, they will not hear you. You find them looking towards you, but they do not see you"
  7,199,Be tolerant; enjoin what is right; and avoid the ignorant
  7,200,"If an evil impulse from Satan provokes you, seek refuge with God; He is all hearing, and all knowing"
  7,201,"When any evil suggestion from Satan touches those who fear God, they are instantly alerted and become watchful"
  7,202,but the followers of devils are led relentlessly into error by them. They never desist
  7,203,"When you do not bring them a sign, they say, \"Why do you not invent one?\" Say, \"I follow only what is revealed to me by my Lord. This Book is an enlightenment from your Lord and a guide and mercy to true believers"
  7,204,"When the Quran is read, listen to it with attention, and hold your peace, so that you may receive mercy"
  7,205,"Remember your Lord deep in your very soul, in all humility and awe, without raising your voice, morning and evening, do not be one of the heedless"
  7,206,"[even] the ones [angels] who live in the presence of your Lord are not too proud to worship Him: they glorify Him and prostrate themselves before Him"